race.comment: TIME TO BACA (4) won a Maiden and then was well fancied last start over 1000m in stronger company, but didn't get into it after spotting them a big start. Draws out today and keeps the handy 3kg claim. A return to form is expected over the longer sprint and with the blinkers on for the first time. SIGNOR BILL (2) needed the run following the switch from a Victorian stable and then improved sharply beaten a whisker in a CL2. Nicely placed to go one better. SABOR (3) is third up and is showing enough to consider. Has been kept on the fresh side and the inside barrier is there to use. NO I'M NOT (6) was plain last time but her Maiden win three back stacks up. Not to be taken lightly.
